						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Kulōttuṅgachōḻa III Year 20: 1198 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. It records a gift of land after purchase from the <hi rend="italic">ūravar</hi> of Kaḍaṟpākkam for burning a twilight lamp to the god Āḷūḍaiyār Tiruvālīśvara-uḍaiyar at Kāṭṭūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rājēndrachōḷanallūr. It is also recorded that the land was freed from taxes.</p>						

